           <h1>US Equity Exposure</h1>
           <p>Hussman Strategic Growth Fund (HSGFX) and James Balance Golden Rainbow (GLRBX) are mainly US equity hedging and balance funds. They had exceptional performance during the 2008 turmoil. </p>
              <ul>
                <li>HSGFX has been fully hedged recently. <a target="_blank" href="${HSGFXRAAanalysis}">See the latest RAA analysis here</a>.</li>
                <li>GLRBX started to decrease its equity exposure since mid of June this year. This is significant as the stock market rose during this period of time. <a target="_blank" href="${GLRBXRAAanalysis}">See the latest RAA analysis here</a>. </li>
              </ul>
           <h1>US Equity Sector Exposure</h1>
           <p>Several stock fund managers exhibit great sector call. Ken Heebner's CGM Focus (CGMFX) is one of them. CGMFX, however, did pay dear during the 2008 financial crash because Heebner made a much early investment into the financial sector. Unfortunately, it has under performed up till now. It has increased its exposure in material sectors dramatically since the end of the June of 2009.</p>
